
All of the following endpoints should have authentication token included in headers.

POST /image
Appends Image table
JSON:
{image}
OUTPUT:
{features_view_url}
Error codes:
- wrong data input (wrong format, too big image etc.)
- unauthorized

GET /images?page=x
Gets list of images for the requesting user using pagination.
JSON:
{user}
OUTPUT:
{
    "images" : [],
    "page": x,
    "pages": 50
}
Error codes:
- forbidden (if no permissions)
- unauthorized

GET /links
Gets links and abilities boolean for the frontend
JSON:
{user.tier}
OUTPUT:
{thumbnail_links: link1, link2...,image_link, expiration_link_bool}
Error codes:
- image post failed(?)
- unauthorized(?)

POST /expiration link
Posts number of seconds typed by user to create expiration link
JSON:
{number_of_seconds}
Error codes:
- wrong format(must be int)
- wrong value(must be between 300-30000)
- unauthorized

GET /expiration link
Gets expiration link for the user
JSON:
{number_of_seconds, image}
OUTPUT:
{expiration_link}
Error codes:
- expiration link post failed(?)
- unauthorized (?)